# Project Architecture

## Three-layer boundary — never cross layers

```
jobs/        → data pipeline only (ingest, calculate, aggregate)
backend/     → API only (FastAPI routers, models, db connection)
frontend/    → UI only (Next.js pages, components, API calls)
```

- `jobs/` never imports from `backend/` or `frontend/`
- `frontend/` never connects to the database directly — only calls FastAPI endpoints
- `backend/` never runs calculations — only reads pre-computed data from DB
- No circular imports between layers

## Business logic placement

- All market data calculations live in `jobs/` (Python)
- All API query logic lives in `backend/routers/`
- All rendering and interaction logic lives in `frontend/`
- SQL views are thin read aliases only — no business logic in the DB

## Repo system rules

- A "repo" is a named pre-aggregated time-series table (date + optional dimensions)
- Repos are always pre-aggregated — never expose `daily_metrics` (stock-level) to users
- Every repo must be registered in the `repos` and `repo_columns` metadata tables
- Adding a new repo = new aggregation script + metadata registration, no API changes needed

## Data source

- Polygon.io is the single data source — no fallbacks, no yfinance, no other providers
- Always use split-adjusted prices (`adjusted=true` on all Polygon calls)
- Index tickers use Polygon's `$I:` prefix (`$I:SPX`, `$I:NDX`, `$I:VIX`)
